Nigeria Immigration Service (NIS) has disassociated itself from a recruitment exercise in circulation, saying there is no recruitment as speculated in some online media reports. “The Comptroller General of Immigration Service, Muhammad Babandede MFR, has become aware that some fraudulent persons are creating the impression that NIS is currently conducting a recruitment exercise. This is NOT TRUE. Members of the public should disregard such offers,” NIS tweeted. Prior to this, NIS recruitment applications were seen on different online media outlets advertising job vacancies in the Nigeria Immigration Service. However, NIS said the job vacancies were not true. Members of the public are advised to disregard the job vacancies. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .